.SH NAME
\fBLockdev\fR be a setgid binary,
which serves up a reliable way ta put a exclusive lock
in /var/lock ta devices (e.g. ttyS0) rockin both FSSTND n' SVr4 methods,
so regular playas don't need write access there.

This task be  bigged up  all up in calls ta tha liblockdev(3) API.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B /usr/sbin/lockdev
.RB [< operation >]
.RB < thang >

.SH DESCRIPTION
Da \fBlockdev\fR command can big-ass up one of tha followin operations (calls ta liblockdev(3) API):

\fB-l\fR - lock thang wit \fBdev_lock()\fR function

\fB-u\fR - unlock thang wit \fBdev_unlock()\fR function

\fBno operation\fR - test lock wit \fBdev_testlock()\fR function

.SH RETURN VALUES
   Value  dev_lock         dev_unlock       dev_testlock
   0      OK               OK               not locked
   1      locked other     locked other     locked
   2      EACCES
   3      EROFS
   4      EFAULT
   5      EINVAL
   6      ENAMETOOLONG
   7      ENOENT
   8      ENOTDIR
   9      ENOMEM
  10      ELOOP
  11      EIO
  12      EPERM
 255      error               error               error

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lockdev (3).
